About ME and the Home: 
(NOTE: A house is just a place to sleep, a HOME is made up of the people in it)

My name is Spencer and I am happy that you have taken an interest in my listing.  Things are always changing and being updated around here, so it is only going to get better! I bought the house in October of 2014, and have been working on it ever since (i.e., bathroom updates, custoom privacy fence, newly constructed pergola, addition of a "mud-room", lighting and painting...the list goes on and doesnt seem to stop!).

I am originally from the south and moved here in 2009.  I graduated from Colorado State University and currently am seeking a graduate degree (part-time).  I work for the U.S. Department of the Interior here in Denver, CO. (Often from home) For those of you who are pet lovers, I just recently welcomed "Lady Emmaline" to my home.  Emma is a Goldendoodle, hypoalergenic, no-shedding, and loves to LOVE.  I should charge more because she is so damn cute! ;).  

I enjoy ALL outdoors.  I am an avid skier, fisherman, hiker, and rock climber.  I also enjoy sipping the astonishing amount of craft beers Denver has to offer.  

I dont find it easy to talk about myself, so please, ask me any questions you may have.  I can tell you what you can expect from me as your host: 
1.  A clean home for your stay;
2.  Safe and comfortable accomadations;
3.  Full access to the the kitchen, living room, your own private bedroom and bathroom as well as outdoor areas (BBQ, Pergola, hammock, fire pit)
4.  Off-street parking (No meters or parking tickets here);
5.  Wifi access and basic cable;
6.  Unlimited LOVE from Emma;
7.  Very kind and friendly (URL HIDDEN)
